OL,5,Cthem'
OL,7,FReflecting on his last memories with
OL,8,Fhis dad, Colin Lamb junior, from
OL,9,FPlumpton, said: "At the time he would
OL,10,Fcome up to me and say 'look after your
OL,11,Fmum, look after your mum'. And I
OL,12,Fthought, what is it?
OL,14,F"What is he talking about? You know,
OL,15,Fwhy's he saying that? Because he knew
OL,16,Fthat something was wrong with that oil
OL,17,Frig."
